lities on the bubble surface grow faster. This may explain the\nabsence of thermal gas in the north-west bubble observed in the Perseus cluster\ncompared to the apparently more disrupted bubbles in the Virgo cluster.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 8 Feb 2005 14:32:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
